<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1346,1877]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1454,1480]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Balthasar" authorityName="Balthasar" authorityYear="1953" box="[324,574,1454,1480]" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klio">
<emphasis box="[324,460,1454,1480]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Chrysis klio</emphasis>
Balthasar
</taxonomicName>
was not included in 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[815,1057,1454,1481]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 232" refId="ref23578" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1959) Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera) mit besonderer Berucksichtigung der europaischen Spezies. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 32 (1), 1 - 232." type="journal article" year="1959">Linsenmaier’s (1959)</bibRefCitation>
revision of the European species and in his supplement (1968). It was taken into consideration only later (
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W." box="[971,1180,1490,1516]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="133 - 158" refId="ref23690" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1987) Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera). 4 Teil. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 60 (1 - 2), 133 - 158." type="journal article" year="1987">Linsenmaier 1987</bibRefCitation>
), when the author provided a diagnostic description. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kimsey, L. S. &amp; Bohart, R. M." box="[506,790,1526,1552]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref23012" refString="Kimsey, L. S. &amp; Bohart, R. M. (1991) The Chrysidid Wasps of the World. Oxford University Press, New York, 652 pp." type="book" year="1991">Kimsey &amp; Bohart (1991)</bibRefCitation>
synonymised it with 
<taxonomicName authority="Abeille de Perrin, 1878" authorityName="Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varidens">
<emphasis box="[1037,1227,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Chrysis varidens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Abeille de Perrin, E." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refId="ref21286" refString="Abeille de Perrin, E. (1878) Diagnoses de Chrysides nouvelles. Published by the author, Marseille, 6 pp." type="book" year="1878">Abeille de Perrin, 1878</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. We checked Balthasar’s 
<typeStatus box="[498,546,1563,1589]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
at MHNP (
<figureCitation box="[678,822,1562,1588]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1064,1088]" captionTargetBox="[157,1432,181,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-20@16.[151,1436,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chrysis klio Balthasar, 1953.A–D, ♂, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal view. B) Head, frontal view. C) Habitus, lateral view. D) Metasoma, postero-lateral view. E) ♂, from Lebanon, genital capsule, ventral view. F–G. ♂, from Sardinia. F) Meta- soma, postero-lateral view. Scale bars 1.0 mm. G) Genital capsule, ventral view. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257727/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 4A–4D</figureCitation>
), and it matches 
<bibRefCitation author="Balthasar, V." box="[1013,1220,1562,1589]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref21586" refString="Balthasar, V. (1953) Monographie des Chrysides de Palestine et des pais limitrophes. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae, 27 (Supplement 2), 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="1953">Balthasar’s (1953)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Linsenmaier, W." pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="133 - 158" refId="ref23690" refString="Linsenmaier, W. (1987) Revision der Familie Chrysididae (Hymenoptera). 4 Teil. Mitteilungen der Schweizerischen Entomologischen Gesellschaft, 60 (1 - 2), 133 - 158." type="journal article" year="1987">Linsenmaier’s (1987)</bibRefCitation>
descriptions, with less contrasting colouring, and with the face, mesopleura, tegula and propodeum green to greenish-gold instead of deep blue. Besides the colour, the two most important diagnostic characters that separate the two species are: (i) the shape of the apical margin of the third metasomal tergum, with four well-formed and visible teeth (
<figureCitation box="[302,390,1706,1732]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1064,1088]" captionTargetBox="[157,1432,181,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-20@16.[151,1436,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chrysis klio Balthasar, 1953.A–D, ♂, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal view. B) Head, frontal view. C) Habitus, lateral view. D) Metasoma, postero-lateral view. E) ♂, from Lebanon, genital capsule, ventral view. F–G. ♂, from Sardinia. F) Meta- soma, postero-lateral view. Scale bars 1.0 mm. G) Genital capsule, ventral view. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257727/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
) (teeth usually like undulations in the typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1878" box="[901,1089,1706,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Masaridae" genus="Chrysis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="varidens">
<emphasis box="[901,1089,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Chrysis varidens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1105,1189,1706,1732]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1064,1088]" captionTargetBox="[157,1432,181,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-20@16.[151,1436,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chrysis klio Balthasar, 1953.A–D, ♂, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal view. B) Head, frontal view. C) Habitus, lateral view. D) Metasoma, postero-lateral view. E) ♂, from Lebanon, genital capsule, ventral view. F–G. ♂, from Sardinia. F) Meta- soma, postero-lateral view. Scale bars 1.0 mm. G) Genital capsule, ventral view. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257727/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
)); (ii) the shape of the male genital capsule, in particular the different shape of the gonocoxa, which is deeply indented between the base of the gonostylus and the upper gonocoxal margin (
<figureCitation box="[728,816,1778,1804]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1064,1088]" captionTargetBox="[157,1432,181,1040]" captionTargetId="figure-20@16.[151,1436,181,1040]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 4. Chrysis klio Balthasar, 1953.A–D, ♂, holotype. A) Habitus, dorsal view. B) Head, frontal view. C) Habitus, lateral view. D) Metasoma, postero-lateral view. E) ♂, from Lebanon, genital capsule, ventral view. F–G. ♂, from Sardinia. F) Meta- soma, postero-lateral view. Scale bars 1.0 mm. G) Genital capsule, ventral view. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6257727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6257727/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 4E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1346,1877]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
We here resurrect 
